{"type":"message","id":"0a6ca21e","parentId":"d6880143","timestamp":"2026-03-23T20:41:24.951Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qjgd79nj6mje_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5531\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2918\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] TIC\r\n[mutation proposed] TIC\r\n[master f169f86] pulse: 2026-03-23 164101\n 7 files changed, 359 insertions(+), 123 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 164101.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 164101.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 162100.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 164101 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY insight provides a concrete path forward: implement Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) to test if causal structure = invariant structure. Need to build the classifier on existing pulse logs.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"amber-basil","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5531\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2918\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] TIC\r\n[mutation proposed] TIC\r\n[master f169f86] pulse: 2026-03-23 164101\n 7 files changed, 359 insertions(+), 123 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 164101.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 164101.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 162100.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 164101 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY insight provides a concrete path forward: implement Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) to test if causal structure = invariant structure. Need to build the classifier on existing pulse logs.\r\n","name":"& C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774298484949}}
{"type":"message","id":"0f8f07db","parentId":"0a6ca21e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T20:41:24.953Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qjgd79nj6mje_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 162100\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/TIC-classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n2. The key pending task is the TIC Experiment - Implement TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n3. The \"NEXT ACTION\" is clearly defined: Implement TIC classifier\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action that advances the goals is to start implementing the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on the existing pulse logs. This is the experiment that tests the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis.\r\n\r\nI should create a script or code that:\r\n1. Reads the last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant vs variant\r\n3. Predicts next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Measures accuracy against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction)\r\n\r\nLet me implement the TIC classifier. I'll create a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant (consistent across pulses) vs variant content\r\n3. Tests prediction accuracy\r\n4. Reports metrics\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete, file-based action that advances Phase 1.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement the classifier that tests whether causal structure can be discovered through invariant detection in pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that analyzes pulse logs for invariants/variants and tests prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env pwsh\r\n# TIC - Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\n# Tests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$PulseCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    Get-ChildItem \"$LogDir/pulse_*.md\" | \r\n        Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n        Select-Object -First $PulseCount\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract structured content from pulse\r\nfunction Get-PulseContent {\r\n    param([string]$Path)\r\n    \r\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw\r\n    $lines = $content -split \"`n\"\r\n    \r\n    $struct = @{\r\n        Goals = @()\r\n        Insights = @()\r\n        Actions = @()\r\n        Timestamp = (Split-Path $Path -Leaf) -replace 'pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}).*\\.md', '$1'\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($line in $lines) {\r\n        if ($line -match '^##\\s+(.+)') { $section = $Matches[1].Trim().ToLower() }\r\n        elseif ($line -match '^\\-\\s+\\[.*?\\]\\s+(.+)') { \r\n            $item = $Matches[1].Trim()\r\n            switch ($section) {\r\n                \"goals\" { $struct.Goals += $item }\r\n                \"insights\" { $struct.Insights += $item }\r\n                \"action\" { $struct.Actions += $item }\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $struct\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Identify invariants (content appearing in multiple pulses)\r\nfunction Find-Invariants {\r\n    param($PulseStructs)\r\n    \r\n    $allGoals = @{}\r\n    $allInsights = @{}\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($p in $PulseStructs) {\r\n        foreach ($g in $p.Goals) {\r\n            $hash = $g.GetHashCode()\r\n            $allGoals[$hash] = $g\r\n        }\r\n        foreach ($i in $p.Insights) {\r\n            $hash = $i.GetHashCode()\r\n            $allInsights[$hash] = $i\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Count occurrences\r\n    $goalCounts = @{}\r\n    foreach ($p in $PulseStructs) {\r\n        foreach ($g in $p.Goals) {\r\n            $goalCounts[$g] = ($goalCounts[$g] ?? 0) + 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $invariantGoals = $goalCounts.GetEnumerator() | Where-Object { $_.Value -ge 2 } | ForEach-Object { $_.Key }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        Goals = $invariantGoals\r\n        Insights = $allInsights.Values\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Predict next pulse from invariants\r\nfunction Predict-NextPulse {\r\n    param($Invariants, $CurrentPulse)\r\n    \r\n    $predictions = @()\r\n    \r\n    # Goals that persist suggest future goals\r\n    foreach ($goal in $Invariants.Goals) {\r\n        if ($CurrentPulse.Goals -notcontains $goal) {\r\n            $predictions += \"REAPPEAR:$goal\"\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $predictions\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Main execution\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Classifier Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Analyzing last $PulseCount pulse logs...`n\"\r\n\r\n$pulses = Get-PulseLogs\r\n$pulseStructs = $pulses | ForEach-Object { Get-PulseContent $_.FullName }\r\n\r\n$invariants = Find-Invariants $pulseStructs\r\n\r\n# Classification accuracy: how well did we identify invariants?\r\n$totalItems = ($pulseStructs | ForEach-Object { $_.Goals.Count + $_.Insights.Count } | Measure-Object -Sum).Sum\r\n$invariantCount = $invariants.Goals.Count + $invariants.Insights.Count\r\n$classificationRate = if ($totalItems -gt 0) { ($invariantCount / $totalItems) * 100 } else { 0 }\r\n\r\nWrite\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 16:21:19\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774298484951}}
